## Known applications page (src/pages/KnownApps.tsx)

Add a new page in the sidebar under CONFIG:
  "Known apps" or "App guides"

This page shows optimization checklists for each supported app.
Each app card has:
  - App name + icon
  - Required Jellyfin settings to change (deep-linked to the right admin page)
  - Status indicators (if reachable via the service group URL, check via API)

### Jellyfin checklist card

Display these items with green/red/amber status indicators.
Check the Jellyfin API at /System/Info (no auth needed) to detect version,
and /System/Configuration (requires API key) to read settings.

Checklist items:
  [ ] Max bitrate = unlimited (0)          — checks /System/Configuration.RemoteClientBitrateLimit
  [ ] Hardware acceleration enabled        — checks /System/Configuration.HardwareAccelerationType
  [ ] Direct play allowed                  — checks /System/Configuration.EnableOriginalTrackTitles
  [ ] Allow direct stream (remux)          — checks playback config
  [ ] Transcode temp on fast storage       — informational, shows configured path
  [ ] BaseURL configured correctly         — checks /System/Configuration.BaseUrl

Required Jellyfin setting (MUST SHOW THIS):
  Jellyfin Admin → Networking → Base URL: set to empty or "/"
  DO NOT set BaseURL unless Jellyfin is hosted at a subpath like example.com/jellyfin
  If BaseURL is set incorrectly, all API calls return 404 even though the proxy is correct.

  Also in Jellyfin Admin → Networking:
    Known proxies: add ProxyGate's internal IP (e.g. 192.168.0.1)
    Allow remote connections: ON
    Enable automatic port mapping: OFF (not needed behind a proxy)

