## Plex-specific notes (same proxy principles, different settings)

Plex also benefits from all Layer 2 proxy optimizations (flushInterval 0ms, long timeouts,
WebSocket support). The main differences:

Required headers for Plex:
```yaml
customRequestHeaders:
  X-Forwarded-Proto: "https"
  X-Plex-Protocol: "1.0"
```

Plex health check path: /identity (not /health)
Returns: XML with machine identifier, no auth required.

Plex network settings (Plex Web → Settings → Remote Access):
  Custom server access URLs: https://plex.example.com:443
  Disable relay: ON (prevents Plex from routing through plex.tv's relay servers)
  LAN Networks: add your LAN CIDR (e.g. 192.168.0.0/24) so local clients get LAN speeds

Plex does NOT need a BaseURL setting. It uses the X-Forwarded-* headers to detect
the proxy and adjust URL generation automatically.
